{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":973,"text":"Good morning."},{"time":2068,"text":"My name is Eric Li, and I was born here."},{"time":7094,"text":"But no, I wasn't born there."},{"time":9803,"text":"This was where I was born:"},{"time":12335,"text":"Shanghai, at the height\nof the Cultural Revolution."},{"time":16308,"text":"My grandmother tells me that she heard"},{"time":18142,"text":"the sound of gunfire\nalong with my first cries."},{"time":21155,"text":"When I was growing up, I was told a story"},{"time":24910,"text":"that explained all I ever\nneeded to know about humanity."},{"time":28515,"text":"It went like this."},{"time":29954,"text":"All human societies develop\nin linear progression,"},{"time":33212,"text":"beginning with primitive\nsociety, then slave society,"},{"time":36804,"text":"feudalism, capitalism, socialism,"},{"time":39835,"text":"and finally, guess where we end up?"},{"time":42179,"text":"Communism!"},{"time":45303,"text":"Sooner or later, all of humanity,"},{"time":49015,"text":"regardless of culture,\nlanguage, nationality,"},{"time":51781,"text":"will arrive at this final stage"},{"time":54237,"text":"of political and social development."},{"time":56670,"text":"The entire world's peoples will be unified"},{"time":58926,"text":"in this paradise on Earth"},{"time":61190,"text":"and live happily ever after."},{"time":63958,"text":"But before we get there, we're engaged"},{"time":66245,"text":"in a struggle between good and evil,"},{"time":68686,"text":"the good of socialism\nagainst the evil of capitalism,"},{"time":71827,"text":"and the good shall triumph."},{"time":73774,"text":"That, of course, was the meta-narrative"},{"time":76270,"text":"distilled from the theories of Karl Marx."},{"time":79050,"text":"And the Chinese bought it."},{"time":81652,"text":"We were taught that grand\nstory day in and day out."},{"time":84565,"text":"It became part of us,\nand we believed in it."},{"time":87338,"text":"The story was a bestseller."},{"time":89532,"text":"About one third of the entire\nworld's population"},{"time":91842,"text":"lived under that meta-narrative."},{"time":94495,"text":"Then, the world changed overnight."},{"time":97262,"text":"As for me, disillusioned\nby the failed religion of my youth,"},{"time":100908,"text":"I went to America and became\na Berkeley hippie."},{"time":103821,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":107020,"text":"Now, as I was coming of age,\nsomething else happened."},{"time":110736,"text":"As if one big story wasn't enough,"},{"time":112932,"text":"I was told another one."},{"time":115444,"text":"This one was just as grand."},{"time":118676,"text":"It also claims that all human societies"},{"time":120839,"text":"develop in a linear progression\ntowards a singular end."},{"time":124684,"text":"This one went as follows:"},{"time":127209,"text":"All societies, regardless of culture,"},{"time":129565,"text":"be it Christian, Muslim, Confucian,"},{"time":132255,"text":"must progress from traditional societies"},{"time":134984,"text":"in which groups are the basic units"},{"time":137530,"text":"to modern societies\nin which atomized individuals"},{"time":141031,"text":"are the sovereign units,"},{"time":142494,"text":"and all these individuals\nare, by definition, rational,"},{"time":146237,"text":"and they all want one thing:"},{"time":148303,"text":"the vote."},{"time":150803,"text":"Because they are all rational,\nonce given the vote,"},{"time":153463,"text":"they produce good government"},{"time":154897,"text":"and live happily ever after."},{"time":157096,"text":"Paradise on Earth, again."},{"time":160015,"text":"Sooner or later, electoral\ndemocracy will be"},{"time":163116,"text":"the only political system\nfor all countries and all peoples,"},{"time":167127,"text":"with a free market to make them all rich."},{"time":169591,"text":"But before we get there,\nwe're engaged in a struggle"},{"time":173141,"text":"between good and evil."},{"time":174834,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":176394,"text":"The good belongs to those\nwho are democracies"},{"time":178632,"text":"and are charged with a mission\nof spreading it"},{"time":180847,"text":"around the globe, sometimes by force,"},{"time":184040,"text":"against the evil of those\nwho do not hold elections."},{"time":187466,"text":"(Video) George H.W. Bush:\nA new world order..."},{"time":189356,"text":"(Video) George W. Bush:...\nending tyranny in our world..."},{"time":192047,"text":"(Video) Barack Obama:...\na single standard for all"},{"time":194500,"text":"who would hold power."},{"time":196840,"text":"Eric X. Li: Now --"},{"time":198644,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":206325,"text":"This story also became a bestseller."},{"time":210348,"text":"According to Freedom House,"},{"time":212215,"text":"the number of democracies\nwent from 45 in 1970"},{"time":215218,"text":"to 115 in 2010."},{"time":217753,"text":"In the last 20 years,\nWestern elites tirelessly"},{"time":220947,"text":"trotted around the globe\nselling this prospectus:"},{"time":224242,"text":"Multiple parties fight for political power"},{"time":226857,"text":"and everyone voting on them"},{"time":228403,"text":"is the only path to salvation"},{"time":230424,"text":"to the long-suffering developing world."},{"time":233191,"text":"Those who buy the prospectus\nare destined for success."},{"time":236303,"text":"Those who do not are doomed to fail."},{"time":239395,"text":"But this time, the Chinese didn't buy it."},{"time":242593,"text":"Fool me once..."},{"time":245112,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":249681,"text":"The rest is history."},{"time":251983,"text":"In just 30 years, China went from"},{"time":253579,"text":"one of the poorest agricultural\ncountries in the world"},{"time":256175,"text":"to its second-largest economy."},{"time":258098,"text":"Six hundred fifty million people"},{"time":260154,"text":"were lifted out of poverty."},{"time":261769,"text":"Eighty percent of the entire\nworld's poverty alleviation"},{"time":264757,"text":"during that period happened in China."},{"time":266982,"text":"In other words, all the new\nand old democracies"},{"time":269631,"text":"put together amounted to a mere fraction"},{"time":272699,"text":"of what a single, one-party\nstate did without voting."},{"time":277968,"text":"See, I grew up on this stuff: food stamps."},{"time":281146,"text":"Meat was rationed to a few hundred grams"},{"time":283079,"text":"per person per month at one point."},{"time":285671,"text":"Needless to say, I ate\nall my grandmother's portions."},{"time":289842,"text":"So I asked myself, what's wrong\nwith this picture?"},{"time":293577,"text":"Here I am in my hometown,"},{"time":295578,"text":"my business growing leaps and bounds."},{"time":297364,"text":"Entrepreneurs are starting\ncompanies every day."},{"time":299663,"text":"Middle class is expanding\nin speed and scale"},{"time":302744,"text":"unprecedented in human history."},{"time":304745,"text":"Yet, according to the grand story,"},{"time":307282,"text":"none of this should be happening."},{"time":310217,"text":"So I went and did the only thing I could.\nI studied it."},{"time":313423,"text":"Yes, China is a one-party state"},{"time":315430,"text":"run by the Chinese Communist\nParty, the Party,"},{"time":319315,"text":"and they don't hold elections."},{"time":321267,"text":"Three assumptions are made"},{"time":323826,"text":"by the dominant political\ntheories of our time."},{"time":326480,"text":"Such a system is operationally rigid,"},{"time":329363,"text":"politically closed,\nand morally illegitimate."},{"time":333049,"text":"Well, the assumptions are wrong."},{"time":336259,"text":"The opposites are true."},{"time":338469,"text":"Adaptability, meritocracy, and legitimacy"},{"time":341807,"text":"are the three defining characteristics"},{"time":343741,"text":"of China's one-party system."},{"time":346112,"text":"Now, most political\nscientists will tell us"},{"time":348184,"text":"that a one-party system\nis inherently incapable"},{"time":351369,"text":"of self-correction."},{"time":353297,"text":"It won't last long\nbecause it cannot adapt."},{"time":355615,"text":"Now here are the facts."},{"time":357413,"text":"In 64 years of running the largest\ncountry in the world,"},{"time":360973,"text":"the range of the Party's policies\nhas been wider"},{"time":363533,"text":"than any other country in recent memory,"},{"time":366450,"text":"from radical land collectivization\nto the Great Leap Forward,"},{"time":370421,"text":"then privatization of farmland,"},{"time":373073,"text":"then the Cultural Revolution,"},{"time":375369,"text":"then Deng Xiaoping's market reform,"},{"time":378065,"text":"then successor Jiang Zemin\ntook the giant political step"},{"time":381478,"text":"of opening up Party membership\nto private businesspeople,"},{"time":384626,"text":"something unimaginable during Mao's rule."},{"time":387689,"text":"So the Party self-corrects\nin rather dramatic fashions."},{"time":391510,"text":"Institutionally, new rules get enacted"},{"time":394140,"text":"to correct previous dysfunctions."},{"time":396719,"text":"For example, term limits."},{"time":398593,"text":"Political leaders used to retain\ntheir positions for life,"},{"time":401379,"text":"and they used that to accumulate power"},{"time":403213,"text":"and perpetuate their rules."},{"time":404782,"text":"Mao was the father of modern China,"},{"time":407002,"text":"yet his prolonged rule led\nto disastrous mistakes."},{"time":409874,"text":"So the Party instituted term limits"},{"time":412034,"text":"with mandatory retirement age of 68 to 70."},{"time":415787,"text":"One thing we often hear is,"},{"time":418036,"text":"\"Political reforms have lagged\nfar behind economic reforms,\""},{"time":421214,"text":"and \"China is in dire need\nof political reform.\""},{"time":424488,"text":"But this claim is a rhetorical trap"},{"time":427447,"text":"hidden behind a political bias."},{"time":430063,"text":"See, some have decided a priori"},{"time":432560,"text":"what kinds of changes they want to see,"},{"time":434442,"text":"and only such changes can\nbe called political reform."},{"time":438049,"text":"The truth is, political\nreforms have never stopped."},{"time":441009,"text":"Compared with 30 years ago,\n20 years, even 10 years ago,"},{"time":444242,"text":"every aspect of Chinese society,"},{"time":446632,"text":"how the country is governed,"},{"time":447504,"text":"from the most local level\nto the highest center,"},{"time":449814,"text":"are unrecognizable today."},{"time":452237,"text":"Now such changes are simply not possible"},{"time":455423,"text":"without political reforms\nof the most fundamental kind."},{"time":459143,"text":"Now I would venture to suggest the Party"},{"time":461336,"text":"is the world's leading\nexpert in political reform."},{"time":465443,"text":"The second assumption\nis that in a one-party state,"},{"time":468475,"text":"power gets concentrated\nin the hands of the few,"},{"time":471206,"text":"and bad governance and corruption follow."},{"time":473908,"text":"Indeed, corruption is a big problem,"},{"time":476081,"text":"but let's first look\nat the larger context."},{"time":478215,"text":"Now, this may be counterintuitive to you."},{"time":480343,"text":"The Party happens to be\none of the most meritocratic"},{"time":483362,"text":"political institutions in the world today."},{"time":486158,"text":"China's highest ruling body,\nthe Politburo, has 25 members."},{"time":490259,"text":"In the most recent one, only five of them"},{"time":492347,"text":"came from a background of privilege,\nso-called princelings."},{"time":495969,"text":"The other 20, including the president\nand the premier,"},{"time":498565,"text":"came from entirely ordinary backgrounds."},{"time":501220,"text":"In the larger central\ncommittee of 300 or more,"},{"time":503661,"text":"the percentage of those who were born"},{"time":505528,"text":"into power and wealth was even smaller."},{"time":507987,"text":"The vast majority\nof senior Chinese leaders"},{"time":510817,"text":"worked and competed their way to the top."},{"time":513462,"text":"Compare that with the ruling elites"},{"time":515594,"text":"in both developed\nand developing countries,"},{"time":517696,"text":"I think you'll find the Party\nbeing near the top"},{"time":520206,"text":"in upward mobility."},{"time":522840,"text":"The question then is,\nhow could that be possible"},{"time":525369,"text":"in a system run by one party?"},{"time":528588,"text":"Now we come to a powerful\npolitical institution,"},{"time":531480,"text":"little-known to Westerners:"},{"time":532997,"text":"the Party's Organization Department."},{"time":535648,"text":"The department functions like a giant"},{"time":537848,"text":"human resource engine\nthat would be the envy"},{"time":540224,"text":"of even some of the most successful\ncorporations."},{"time":543554,"text":"It operates a rotating pyramid"},{"time":545823,"text":"made up of three components:"},{"time":547190,"text":"civil service, state-owned enterprises,"},{"time":549746,"text":"and social organizations like a university"},{"time":551990,"text":"or a community program."},{"time":554128,"text":"They form separate\nyet integrated career paths"},{"time":556639,"text":"for Chinese officials."},{"time":558543,"text":"They recruit college grads\ninto entry-level positions"},{"time":561628,"text":"in all three tracks,\nand they start from the bottom,"},{"time":564378,"text":"called \"keyuan\" [clerk]."},{"time":565934,"text":"Then they could get promoted"},{"time":567317,"text":"through four increasingly elite ranks:"},{"time":572433,"text":"fuke [deputy section manager], ke [section manager], fuchu\n[deputy division manager], and chu [division manger]."},{"time":575745,"text":"Now these are not moves\nfrom \"Karate Kid,\" okay?"},{"time":578055,"text":"It's serious business."},{"time":581399,"text":"The range of positions is wide,"},{"time":583736,"text":"from running health care in a village"},{"time":585522,"text":"to foreign investment in a city district"},{"time":587583,"text":"to manager in a company."},{"time":589708,"text":"Once a year, the department\nreviews their performance."},{"time":592304,"text":"They interview\ntheir superiors, their peers,"},{"time":594639,"text":"their subordinates. They vet\ntheir personal conduct."},{"time":597420,"text":"They conduct public opinion surveys."},{"time":599452,"text":"Then they promote the winners."},{"time":601415,"text":"Throughout their careers, these cadres"},{"time":603249,"text":"can move\nthrough and out of all three tracks."},{"time":606083,"text":"Over time, the good ones move\nbeyond the four base levels"},{"time":608961,"text":"to the fuju [deputy bureau chief]\nand ju [bureau chief] levels."},{"time":611985,"text":"There, they enter high officialdom."},{"time":614497,"text":"By that point, a typical\nassignment will be"},{"time":616657,"text":"to manage a district\nwith a population in the millions"},{"time":619516,"text":"or a company with hundreds\nof millions of dollars in revenue."},{"time":623047,"text":"Just to show you\nhow competitive the system is,"},{"time":626976,"text":"in 2012, there were 900,000\nfuke and ke levels,"},{"time":630694,"text":"600,000 fuchu and chu levels,"},{"time":633518,"text":"and only 40,000 fuju and ju levels."},{"time":636953,"text":"After the ju levels,"},{"time":638681,"text":"the best few move further\nup several more ranks,"},{"time":641282,"text":"and eventually make it\nto the Central Committee."},{"time":644413,"text":"The process takes two to three decades."},{"time":647165,"text":"Does patronage play a role?\nYes, of course."},{"time":650274,"text":"But merit remains the fundamental driver."},{"time":653846,"text":"In essence, the Organization\nDepartment runs"},{"time":656376,"text":"a modernized version\nof China's centuries-old"},{"time":658849,"text":"mentoring system."},{"time":660913,"text":"China's new president, Xi Jinping,"},{"time":663004,"text":"is the son of a former leader,\nwhich is very unusual,"},{"time":665583,"text":"first of his kind to make the top job."},{"time":667803,"text":"Even for him, the career took 30 years."},{"time":670698,"text":"He started as a village manager,"},{"time":672566,"text":"and by the time he entered the Politburo,"},{"time":674543,"text":"he had managed areas\nwith a total population"},{"time":676684,"text":"of 150 million people"},{"time":678288,"text":"and combined GDPs of 1.5 trillion U.S.\ndollars."},{"time":682734,"text":"Now, please don't get me wrong, okay?"},{"time":685054,"text":"This is not a put-down of anyone.\nIt's just a statement of fact."},{"time":688308,"text":"George W. Bush, remember him?"},{"time":692142,"text":"This is not a put-down."},{"time":694583,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":695388,"text":"Before becoming governor of Texas,"},{"time":698487,"text":"or Barack Obama\nbefore running for president,"},{"time":701106,"text":"could not make even a small county manager"},{"time":703865,"text":"in China's system."},{"time":705793,"text":"Winston Churchill once said that democracy"},{"time":707817,"text":"is a terrible system\nexcept for all the rest."},{"time":710134,"text":"Well, apparently he hadn't heard\nof the Organization Department."},{"time":714415,"text":"Now, Westerners always assume that"},{"time":716759,"text":"multi-party election\nwith universal suffrage"},{"time":719777,"text":"is the only source\nof political legitimacy."},{"time":722919,"text":"I was asked once, \"The Party\nwasn't voted in by election."},{"time":726281,"text":"Where is the source of legitimacy?\""},{"time":728511,"text":"I said, \"How about competency?\""},{"time":732073,"text":"We all know the facts."},{"time":733550,"text":"In 1949, when the Party took power,"},{"time":735491,"text":"China was mired in civil wars,\ndismembered by foreign aggression,"},{"time":738818,"text":"average life expectancy\nat that time, 41 years old."},{"time":743113,"text":"Today, it's the second largest\neconomy in the world,"},{"time":746023,"text":"an industrial powerhouse,\nand its people live"},{"time":748626,"text":"in increasing prosperity."},{"time":750713,"text":"Pew Research polls Chinese\npublic attitudes,"},{"time":753866,"text":"and here are the numbers in recent years."},{"time":755923,"text":"Satisfaction with the direction\nof the country: 85 percent."},{"time":760423,"text":"Those who think they're better\noff than five years ago:"},{"time":763067,"text":"70 percent."},{"time":764998,"text":"Those who expect the future to be better:"},{"time":767382,"text":"a whopping 82 percent."},{"time":770046,"text":"Financial Times polls\nglobal youth attitudes,"},{"time":773575,"text":"and these numbers, brand new,\njust came from last week."},{"time":776990,"text":"Ninety-three percent\nof China's Generation Y"},{"time":779772,"text":"are optimistic\nabout their country's future."},{"time":782358,"text":"Now, if this is not legitimacy,\nI'm not sure what is."},{"time":788246,"text":"In contrast, most electoral\ndemocracies around the world"},{"time":791415,"text":"are suffering from dismal performance."},{"time":793518,"text":"I don't need to elaborate\nfor this audience"},{"time":795833,"text":"how dysfunctional it is,\nfrom Washington to European capitals."},{"time":800170,"text":"With a few exceptions, the vast number"},{"time":803059,"text":"of developing countries that have\nadopted electoral regimes"},{"time":805966,"text":"are still suffering\nfrom poverty and civil strife."},{"time":809777,"text":"Governments get elected,\nand then they fall"},{"time":811849,"text":"below 50 percent approval in a few months"},{"time":814452,"text":"and stay there and get worse\nuntil the next election."},{"time":818000,"text":"Democracy is becoming a perpetual cycle"},{"time":820423,"text":"of elect and regret."},{"time":822801,"text":"At this rate, I'm afraid it is democracy,"},{"time":826330,"text":"not China's one-party\nsystem, that is in danger"},{"time":828950,"text":"of losing legitimacy."},{"time":831209,"text":"Now, I don't want to create\nthe misimpression"},{"time":834059,"text":"that China's hunky-dory, on the way"},{"time":836067,"text":"to some kind of superpowerdom."},{"time":837860,"text":"The country faces enormous challenges."},{"time":840819,"text":"The social and economic problems that come"},{"time":842843,"text":"with wrenching change\nlike this are mind-boggling."},{"time":846728,"text":"Pollution is one. Food safety.\nPopulation issues."},{"time":850275,"text":"On the political front, the worst\nproblem is corruption."},{"time":854222,"text":"Corruption is widespread\nand undermines the system"},{"time":857054,"text":"and its moral legitimacy."},{"time":858856,"text":"But most analysts misdiagnose the disease."},{"time":861703,"text":"They say that corruption is the result\nof the one-party system,"},{"time":864612,"text":"and therefore, in order to cure it,"},{"time":866303,"text":"you have to do away\nwith the entire system."},{"time":868375,"text":"But a more careful look\nwould tell us otherwise."},{"time":871252,"text":"Transparency International ranks China"},{"time":874172,"text":"between 70 and 80 in recent\nyears among 170 countries,"},{"time":877938,"text":"and it's been moving up."},{"time":880115,"text":"India, the largest democracy in the world,"},{"time":882178,"text":"94 and dropping."},{"time":884325,"text":"For the hundred or so countries\nthat are ranked below China,"},{"time":887207,"text":"more than half of them\nare electoral democracies."},{"time":889796,"text":"So if election is the panacea\nfor corruption,"},{"time":893091,"text":"how come these countries can't fix it?"},{"time":896334,"text":"Now, I'm a venture capitalist.\nI make bets."},{"time":899928,"text":"It wouldn't be fair\nto end this talk without"},{"time":902260,"text":"putting myself on the line\nand making some predictions."},{"time":904904,"text":"So here they are."},{"time":906609,"text":"In the next 10 years, China\nwill surpass the U.S."},{"time":909411,"text":"and become the largest\neconomy in the world."},{"time":911788,"text":"Income per capita will be near the top"},{"time":913869,"text":"of all developing countries."},{"time":916051,"text":"Corruption will be curbed,\nbut not eliminated,"},{"time":918373,"text":"and China will move up 10 to 20 notches"},{"time":920786,"text":"to above 60 in T.I. ranking."},{"time":923628,"text":"Economic reform will accelerate,\npolitical reform will continue,"},{"time":926700,"text":"and the one-party system will hold firm."},{"time":930056,"text":"We live in the dusk of an era."},{"time":933214,"text":"Meta-narratives that make universal claims"},{"time":936499,"text":"failed us in the 20th century"},{"time":938460,"text":"and are failing us in the 21st."},{"time":941244,"text":"Meta-narrative is the cancer"},{"time":943838,"text":"that is killing democracy from the inside."},{"time":946645,"text":"Now, I want to clarify something."},{"time":948412,"text":"I'm not here to make\nan indictment of democracy."},{"time":950932,"text":"On the contrary, I think\ndemocracy contributed"},{"time":953525,"text":"to the rise of the West\nand the creation of the modern world."},{"time":956721,"text":"It is the universal claim\nthat many Western elites"},{"time":959832,"text":"are making about their political\nsystem, the hubris,"},{"time":963321,"text":"that is at the heart\nof the West's current ills."},{"time":966560,"text":"If they would spend\njust a little less time"},{"time":968865,"text":"on trying to force their way onto others,"},{"time":971005,"text":"and a little bit more\non political reform at home,"},{"time":974672,"text":"they might give their democracy\na better chance."},{"time":978062,"text":"China's political model\nwill never supplant"},{"time":980440,"text":"electoral democracy,\nbecause unlike the latter,"},{"time":982760,"text":"it doesn't pretend to be universal."},{"time":984717,"text":"It cannot be exported. But\nthat is the point precisely."},{"time":988549,"text":"The significance of China's example"},{"time":991148,"text":"is not that it provides an alternative,"},{"time":993115,"text":"but the demonstration\nthat alternatives exist."},{"time":997555,"text":"Let us draw to a close this\nera of meta-narratives."},{"time":1001189,"text":"Communism and democracy may\nboth be laudable ideals,"},{"time":1004552,"text":"but the era of their dogmatic\nuniversalism is over."},{"time":1008653,"text":"Let us stop telling\npeople and our children"},{"time":1011140,"text":"there's only one way to govern ourselves"},{"time":1013392,"text":"and a singular future towards which"},{"time":1015201,"text":"all societies must evolve."},{"time":1017583,"text":"It is wrong. It is irresponsible."},{"time":1020378,"text":"And worst of all, it is boring."},{"time":1024616,"text":"Let universality make way for plurality."},{"time":1028535,"text":"Perhaps a more interesting age is upon us."},{"time":1031732,"text":"Are we brave enough to welcome it?"},{"time":1033944,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1035138,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1051158,"text":"Thank you. Thank you. Thank you. Thanks."},{"time":1054794,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Eric, stay\nwith me for a couple of minutes,"},{"time":1057000,"text":"because I want to ask you\na couple of questions."},{"time":1059714,"text":"I think many here, and in general\nin Western countries,"},{"time":1063242,"text":"would agree with your statement\nabout analysis"},{"time":1066644,"text":"of democratic systems\nbecoming dysfunctional,"},{"time":1069349,"text":"but at the same time,\nmany would kind of find"},{"time":1072276,"text":"unsettling the thought\nthat there is an unelected"},{"time":1076221,"text":"authority that, without any form\nof oversight or consultation,"},{"time":1081617,"text":"decides what the national interest is."},{"time":1084532,"text":"What is the mechanism in the Chinese model"},{"time":1087534,"text":"that allows people to say, actually,"},{"time":1089753,"text":"the national interest\nas you defined it is wrong?"},{"time":1092340,"text":"EXL: You know, Frank Fukuyama,\nthe political scientist,"},{"time":1096402,"text":"called the Chinese system\n\"responsive authoritarianism.\""},{"time":1100246,"text":"It's not exactly right,\nbut I think it comes close."},{"time":1103356,"text":"So I know the largest public\nopinion survey company"},{"time":1107330,"text":"in China, okay?"},{"time":1109212,"text":"Do you know who their biggest client is?"},{"time":1111892,"text":"The Chinese government."},{"time":1113738,"text":"Not just from the central government,"},{"time":1116204,"text":"the city government,\nthe provincial government,"},{"time":1117628,"text":"to the most local neighborhood districts."},{"time":1119707,"text":"They conduct surveys all the time."},{"time":1121850,"text":"Are you happy with the garbage collection?"},{"time":1124460,"text":"Are you happy with the general\ndirection of the country?"},{"time":1126572,"text":"So there is, in China, there\nis a different kind of mechanism"},{"time":1129833,"text":"to be responsive to the demands\nand the thinking of the people."},{"time":1133394,"text":"My point is, I think we should get unstuck"},{"time":1136602,"text":"from the thinking\nthat there's only one political system --"},{"time":1139033,"text":"election, election, election --"},{"time":1140578,"text":"that could make it responsive."},{"time":1142306,"text":"I'm not sure, actually, elections produce"},{"time":1144290,"text":"responsive government\nanymore in the world."},{"time":1147236,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1151943,"text":"BG: Many seem to agree."},{"time":1153103,"text":"One of the features of a democratic system"},{"time":1155759,"text":"is a space for civil\nsociety to express itself."},{"time":1159028,"text":"And you have shown figures\nabout the support"},{"time":1161396,"text":"that the government\nand the authorities have in China."},{"time":1164300,"text":"But then you've just\nmentioned other elements"},{"time":1167605,"text":"like, you know, big challenges,\nand there are, of course,"},{"time":1169759,"text":"a lot of other data that go\nin a different direction:"},{"time":1172685,"text":"tens of thousands of unrests and protests"},{"time":1175342,"text":"and environmental protests, etc."},{"time":1178201,"text":"So you seem to suggest the Chinese model"},{"time":1181217,"text":"doesn't have a space outside of the Party"},{"time":1183328,"text":"for civil society to express itself."},{"time":1185629,"text":"EXL: There's a vibrant\ncivil society in China,"},{"time":1189807,"text":"whether it's environment or what-have-you."},{"time":1191436,"text":"But it's different. You\nwouldn't recognize it."},{"time":1193684,"text":"Because, by Western definitions,\na so-called civil society"},{"time":1196566,"text":"has to be separate or even in opposition"},{"time":1199410,"text":"to the political system,"},{"time":1201101,"text":"but that concept is alien\nfor Chinese culture."},{"time":1205866,"text":"For thousands of years,\nyou have civil society,"},{"time":1208339,"text":"yet they are consistent and coherent"},{"time":1210828,"text":"and part of a political order, and I think"},{"time":1213675,"text":"it's a big cultural difference."},{"time":1217045,"text":"BG: Eric, thank you for sharing\nthis with TED. EXL: Thank you."}]}]}